cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE, cs.SI 

The paper proposes a deep neural network-based method for converting single polarization grayscale SAR image to fully polarimetric. This involves feature extraction and translation, which are common techniques in computer vision and machine learning, hence the high likelihood of cs.CV and cs.LG. The paper also involves image processing and signal processing techniques, which are relevant to cs.IR and cs.SI. Finally, the use of neural networks for reconstruction of full-pol data from compact-pol data suggests a potential application in neural networks for signal processing, hence the likelihood of cs.NE.
